results.t: ENGAGE | definition in the Cambridge English Dictionary
results.p: engage verb (EMPLOY) ... to arrange to employ someone; hire: She decided to engage a personal assistant. Her family engaged a tutor to teach her French.
verb (used without object) · to occupy oneself; become involved: to engage in business or politics. · to take employment: She engaged in her mother's business.
Other forms: engaged; engaging; engages. Engage means to bind, catch, or involve. If your sink is stopped up, engage, or hire, a plumber to fix it.
